The course deals with concept and scope of contract law; questions concerning the conclusion, execution and breach of a contract; the rights and duties of the parties. Major types of contracts will be covered also.Objectives/eesmärkid:  General purpose of the course is to provide primary knowledge about law of contracts, basic legal terms and principles, questions concerning conclusion, execution and breach of contracts, and describe the major types of contracts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student has acquired basic knowledge and skills of contract law. At the end of the course a student
-	knows basic terms and principles of contract law
-	knows major types of contracts
-	has primary skills to solve practical problems and cases arising
